<br>
As always, well thought-out work.<br>
<br>
I concur about the need to make SBs more group attractive to the unknowledgeable… a truly knowledgeable and careful SB can be very useful to a party (debuff styles for high damage while not getting agro), but it seems that too many parties have grouped with poorly skilled SBs and are in once-burnt-twice-shy mode.  There's lots of stupid AE Hammers Thanes out there that break mez, but Thanes still get group cause of pulling/tanking/Protect/etc. ability.<br>
<br>
I liked it the first time, and still like the idea of Snowsquall popping BT for RvR stuff, I see no reason to think that this would pose any problem or concerns for imbalance.  Most SBs will open with a Crit move, but for those that don’t go Crit or Zerks then this makes it a good alternative to chase down those running casters or parties with pulsing BT.  I think I already mentioned it, but would it be possible to also lobby for the second in the chain Snowsquall -&gt; Icy Brilliance to have a small detaunt on Icy?  This would have zero impact on RvR and very nice benefit in PvE grouping.  It would be more helpful in the lower levels for SBs to have a simple LA detaunt move (so that they wouldn't kill the group as much while they are n00bs... but bleed on Snowsquall is nice).<br>
<br>
All the discussion on grouping is written out in all it’s gory glory at the following:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/nage42/ShadowBlade/shadowblades_on_the_exp_treadmill.htm">www.geocities.com/nage42/...admill.htm</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
Old hat to the knowledgeable, just wish the n00bs would do it so that we stop getting groups saying &quot;don’t need an SB, they get the party killed&quot;.<br>
<br>
Good luck Braack, I hope that the Mythic style team goes over the opener reqs and duplicate effects for base-wep, CS, and LA moves (and takes away one-chain stunning moves… but whatever.<br>
<br>
As an aside, there is probably one thing that should be removed from stealthers in the spirit of realism.  When a character is stealthed and they fall (you get the Safe_Fall message), then they should probably pop out of stealth and be on a 3-5 second timer to restealth.  Having stealthers jump (far) off keep walls to get behind and BSII door bangers then climb back up wall is just silly… it’s not fair to tank classes.  Now if you climb down then that’s cool, but please, jumping off and staying stealthed from a really long fall is a little unrealistic.  I think we can throw non-stealthers a bone and show that we are willing to be reasonable with things that are too powerful if they stop taking away (fix) things that we need.<br>
<br>
Just my thoughts.<br>
<br>
